'''Ann Pellegrini''' is Professor of [[Performance Studies]] ([[Tisch School of the Arts]]) and Social and Cultural Analysis (Faculty of Arts and Science) at [[NYU]] and the director of NYU's Center for the Study of Gender and Sexuality.<ref>{{cite web|title=Faculty and Staff {{!}} CSGS Center for the Study of Gender and Sexuality at New York University|url=http://www.csgsnyu.org/about/faculty-and-staff/|website=www.csgsnyu.org|publisher=New York University|accessdate=24 June 2017}}</ref> In 1998, she founded the Sexual Cultures book series at [[NYU Press]] with [[José Esteban Muñoz|José Muñoz]];<ref>{{cite web|title=Sexual Cultures - NYU Press|url=https://nyupress.org/series/sexual-cultures/|website=nyupress.org|publisher=New York University|accessdate=24 June 2017|language=en}}</ref> she now co-edits the series with Joshua Takano Chambers-Letson and [[Tavia Nyong'o]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ann Pellegrini|url=https://tisch.nyu.edu/about/directory/performance-studies/92968907|website=tisch.nyu.edu|publisher=New York University|accessdate=24 June 2017}}</ref> Her book ''You Can Tell Just By Looking'', co-authored with Michael Bronski and Michael Amico, was a finalist for the 2014 [[Lambda Literary Award]] for Best LGBT Non-Fiction.<ref>{{cite web|title=26th Annual Lambda Literary Award Finalists and Winners|url=http://www.lambdaliterary.org/26th-annual-lambda-literary-award-finalists-and-winners/|website=Lambda Literary|accessdate=24 June 2017|date=7 March 2014}}</ref>
Pellegrini has undergraduate degrees from [[Harvard College]] and [[Oxford University]]. She then earned an M.A. and Ph.D. from [[Harvard University]].
