'''Cheng Beng Buddhist Society''', also the [[Vimalakirti]] Buddhist Centre ({{zh|s=净名佛学社}}), is a [[Buddhist]] monastery in [[Singapore]]. The foundation was originally set up by Venerable [[Wen Ming Hu]]. The present premises are located at [[Geylang]], Singapore.

==History==

Cheng Beng Buddhist Society was founded as Singapore Buddhist Youth Group in 1961 by Wen Ming Hu and other lay Buddhists, and was renamed under its present name in 1962 when it was also relocated at an address offered by [[Chen Lu Niang]]. The society was named after the Buddhist [[bodhisattva]] [[Vimalakirti]], a householder devotee of the ancient [[Shakyamuni Buddha]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Thurman|first1=Robert A. F.|title=VIMALAKIRTI NIRDESA SUTRA|date=1976|publisher=The Pennsylvania State University|url=http://www2.kenyon.edu/Depts/Religion/Fac/Adler/Reln260/Vimalakirti.htm|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref>

==Present Day==
Building expansion took place from 2002 onwards which saw a six-story building completed.

On 4 March 2012 the present day name of Vimalakirti Buddhist Centre was adopted.<ref>{{cite web | title = Our History | publisher = Vimalakirti Buddhist Centre | url = http://vbc.org.sg/about-us/our-history/ | accessdate = 2014-09-10 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140911001739/http://vbc.org.sg/about-us/our-history/ | archivedate = 2014-09-11 | df =  }}</ref>

Occasional Buddhist workshops and services catering towards the lay Buddhist community are offered on its premises.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chodron|first1=Thubten|title=01-06-13 Dealing with Grief and Loss|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=maGlnNF2z3U|website=Youtube|publisher=Sravasti Abbey|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Tan|first1=Chade Meng|title=Becoming an Outstanding Leader as a Buddhist|url=http://now-events.net/sg/page/1140249|publisher=East Integration Technologies|accessdate=6 November 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106061001/http://now-events.net/sg/page/1140249|archivedate=6 November 2014|df=}}</ref> The centre also hosts the ''Cakkavala Meditation Centre''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Membership|url=http://www.cakkavala.org/Members.htm|website=Cakkavala Meditation Centre|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref>

