'''Footreading''', also known as "'''solestry'''" (coined from ''[[Sole (foot)|sole]]'', on the analogy of ''[[palmistry]]''), is a [[Method of divination|method]] of [[divination]] by means of the [[foot]]. It involves the observation and interpretation of foot structure, skin (e.g., texture, blemishes, pigmentation) and [[toe nail]]s, which are believed to reflect a person's emotions or [[Personality psychology|character]].<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Bosmia |first=Anand N. |last2=Bosmia |first2=Arpan N. |last3=Tubbs |first3=R. S. |date=2017-10-01 |title=The Foot-Reading Cult of Japan |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10943-013-9736-8 |journal=Journal of Religion and Health |language=en |volume=56 |issue=5 |pages=1600–1604 |doi=10.1007/s10943-013-9736-8 |issn=0022-4197}}</ref>
