'''Rustam II''' ({{lang-fa|رستم}}), was the twelfth ruler of the [[Bavand dynasty]] from 964 to 979. He was the brother and successor of [[Shahriyar II]].

Rustam was the son of [[Sharwin II]]. In 964, Shahriyar was deposed because of his pro-[[Ziyarid]] policies in favor of his pro-[[Buyid]] brother Rustam. Rustam was the first Bavand ruler who embraced [[Shia Islam]]. Shahriyar later tried to reclaim the Bavand throne by invading [[Tabaristan]] with a [[Samanid]] army in 968, but with no avail. Rustam died in 979, and was succeeded by his son [[Al-Marzuban]].

